         <div>
            <head>15.1.1881 Samstag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49096">Paris</placeName> 15 January
      1881 Saturday</p>
            <p>We went to the <placeName key="56724">catacombes</placeName> today. Everybody has got a
      light and the descent begins, we go down 80 steps and penetrate into a long
      corridor chiselled out of the rock, everybody laughing and talking and joking
      but as we come in sight of an enormous black porch with bone on bone scull next
      to scull and an inscription of which I can only remember the beginning:
      &#x201e;<foreign n="fr">Ils furent ce que nous sommes, poussierre de la terre, jouet de vents
         .............</foreign>&#x201c; everybody stops one feels that one is in the vestibule of
      death we go through the porch and on the other side nothing but bones and
      sculls in these six words one can explain all the <placeName key="56724">catacombes</placeName>. Here and there some very pretty inscriptions such
               as &#x201e;<foreign n="fr">Homme n&#x2019;oublié pas que tu dois mourir</foreign>&#x201c; and
      others here and there passages like ours branching off we pass by a small kind
      of a room where crosses are made out of scull and by pitt full of water at last
      we come out of this dreadfull passage by another black door and porch and go
      into another corridor under two natural &#x201e;<foreign n="fr">cloches</foreign>&#x201c; or bells formed
      by the earth falling down after some time we come to a staircase and we got out
      at last after having mounted the same number of steps as before, &#x201e;<foreign n="fr">des
         cranes, des cranes et encore des cranes</foreign>&#x201c; ought to be the inscription on
      it.</p>
